parameters.name: TIME_TAG
parameters.description:
A derived value for the time tag associated
      with the data values in each record.                              
      The derived value is created by the following formula:               
      MET + 0.05 * delta_ts + 0.5 + (dt_sample)*(i-1)*(num_samples/num_AC).
      MET is the mission elapsed time for the entire science packet.       
      delta_ts is the time in seconds between the MET and the first sample 
      in the science packet.                                               
      dt_sample is the time between samples in seconds and is given by     
      dt_sample = 1/sample_rate where sample_rate is the reported sample   
      rate in samples per second.                                          
      num_samples is number of magnetometer samples.                       
      num_AC is the number of logAC values.                                
      i is the incremental counter for each of the logAC values. i=1 is the
      first logAC value in the science packet.

parameters.name: AC_AXIS
parameters.description: AC axis selected. =0 X, =1 Y, =2 Z

parameters.name: B_AC
parameters.description:
Average output amplitude in units
            of nano-Tesla of a 1-to-10 Hz bandpass filter for the selected
            magnetometer axis selected by command.
